# Postgres Standards

## Modeling

- Explicit constraints (PK, FK, unique, checks)
- Timestamps (`created_at` / `updated_at`) as project convention
- Soft delete when domain needs history/recovery
- Indexes for real filter/sort/search paths
- Multi-tenant columns (`org_id`, etc.) on tenant data

## Queries

- Select only needed columns when performance matters
- Paginate large sets
- Prefer RPC for complex authorized operations when the repo already uses it
- Never bypass tenancy filters

## Migrations

Additive, reviewable, named clearly. Do not edit old applied migrations casually on shared environments.
